20/03/2007
TIRANA, Albania -- President Alfred Moisiu and the Albanian Parliament approved on Monday (March 19th) Prime Minister Sali Berisha's recent government reshuffle and the appointment of several new ministers. The changes include the appointment of Nard Ndoka as health minister, Majlinda Bregu as integration minister, Gazmend Oketa as deputy prime minister, Ilir Rusmajli as justice minister and Ylli Pango as tourism minister. 
After winning approval in Parliament, Berisha promised that the cabinet would work hard to complete set reforms, especially those involving property and fiscal reforms. He also urged the opposition to co-operate in the decentralisation process. (Albanian News - 20/03/07; Top-Channel, Albanian President website - 19/03/07)
